HEADWORD: Gagger
<hw>Gag"ger</hw> <pr>(g⟦acr⟧g"g⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who gags.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>A piece of iron imbedded in
the sand of a mold to keep the sand in place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gaggle</ent>⟦br⟧
